A Transport Department official says government lacks the capacity to deal with conflict in the taxi industry. Deputy director for conflict resolution, registration and monitoring, Peter Dhlamini, testified before the commission of inquiry into taxi violence. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The commission looking into taxi violence in Gauteng is already bearing fruit. Commission spokesperson Koena Moabelo says there's already been a decrease in violent incidents. READ: Brick-throwing taxi driver arrested The inquiry is looking into the reasons behind taxi violence. "Since the commission started sitting, the violence has gone down, that's one of the impacts that the commission has already brought," Moabelo said.